{
  "video_id": "DnSmGFmP8qU",
  "title": "Frankenstein: The Modern Prometheus - Extra Sci Fi - #1",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 699.0,
      "end_time": 3532.0,
      "text": "Science fiction\nbegins with Frankenstein."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 3532.0,
      "end_time": 5628.0,
      "text": "So many of the ideas, and the tropes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 5628.0,
      "end_time": 8116.0,
      "text": "even the philosophy behind\nscience fiction come"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 8116.0,
      "end_time": 10818.0,
      "text": "from this one great work."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 10818.0,
      "end_time": 14985.0,
      "text": "So let us start where we\nmust, and talk Frankenstein."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 21024.0,
      "end_time": 22717.0,
      "text": "The very first sentence of the preface"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 22717.0,
      "end_time": 24653.0,
      "text": "to Frankenstein reads thus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 24653.0,
      "end_time": 26723.0,
      "text": "\"The event on which\nthis fiction is founded,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 26723.0,
      "end_time": 29415.0,
      "text": "\"has been supposed, by\nDr. Darwin, and some of"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 29415.0,
      "end_time": 31323.0,
      "text": "\"the physiological writers of Germany,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 31323.0,
      "end_time": 34104.0,
      "text": "\"as not of impossible occurrence."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 34104.0,
      "end_time": 36351.0,
      "text": "\"I shall not be supposed as\naccording the remotest degree"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 36351.0,
      "end_time": 39089.0,
      "text": "\"of serious faith to such an imagination,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 39089.0,
      "end_time": 42210.0,
      "text": "\"yet, in assuming it as the\nbasis of a work of fancy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 42210.0,
      "end_time": 45289.0,
      "text": "\"I have not considered\nmyself as merely weaving"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 45289.0,
      "end_time": 48240.0,
      "text": "\"a series of supernatural terrors.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 48240.0,
      "end_time": 49909.0,
      "text": "And it is on that statement that all"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 49909.0,
      "end_time": 52870.0,
      "text": "of science fiction is founded."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 52870.0,
      "end_time": 54675.0,
      "text": "Shelley is saying that\nthe events in this book"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 54675.0,
      "end_time": 56975.0,
      "text": "could be real, not that they are real"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 56975.0,
      "end_time": 58863.0,
      "text": "or even that they are remotely likely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 58863.0,
      "end_time": 61970.0,
      "text": "but they could exist in\nthe universe we know."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 61970.0,
      "end_time": 63733.0,
      "text": "Eventually, we will escape the bounds of"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 63733.0,
      "end_time": 65705.0,
      "text": "this statement with science fiction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 65705.0,
      "end_time": 68393.0,
      "text": "but it's this idea, the\nidea that our sci-fi"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 68393.0,
      "end_time": 71458.0,
      "text": "tales exist within our rational world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 71458.0,
      "end_time": 74404.0,
      "text": "within the bounds of what\nscience tells us is possible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 74404.0,
      "end_time": 77122.0,
      "text": "that makes science fiction\ndifferent fundamentally different"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 77122.0,
      "end_time": 79095.0,
      "text": "from fantasy or myth."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 79095.0,
      "end_time": 80893.0,
      "text": "And that thought is incredibly important"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 80893.0,
      "end_time": 82922.0,
      "text": "at the birth of the genre."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 82922.0,
      "end_time": 85028.0,
      "text": "This is what separates it\nout as its own distinct"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 85028.0,
      "end_time": 87603.0,
      "text": "literary branch and\nallows it to have rules"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 87603.0,
      "end_time": 90460.0,
      "text": "and conventions unlike those\nalready existing genres"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 90460.0,
      "end_time": 94787.0,
      "text": "of the fantastic, of\nhorror or folklore or myth."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 94787.0,
      "end_time": 97616.0,
      "text": "It's also initially part\nof what gets us to buy in."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 97616.0,
      "end_time": 102116.0,
      "text": "Science fiction uses the\npossible as a lens for our world."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 102116.0,
      "end_time": 104489.0,
      "text": "It may be the remote and the unlikely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 104489.0,
      "end_time": 107665.0,
      "text": "but what better way to\nlook at human nature than"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 107665.0,
      "end_time": 110475.0,
      "text": "to set it against the\nextreme cases of what"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 110475.0,
      "end_time": 114729.0,
      "text": "it might someday encounter\nand see what rolls out."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 114729.0,
      "end_time": 117016.0,
      "text": "This is so important to Shelley that it's"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 117016.0,
      "end_time": 120022.0,
      "text": "the very first thing that's\npresented to the reader."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 120022.0,
      "end_time": 122660.0,
      "text": "Without this idea of\nthe fantastic possible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 122660.0,
      "end_time": 125272.0,
      "text": "I don't think we have science fiction."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 125272.0,
      "end_time": 127972.0,
      "text": "But that is far from the\nonly standard Frankenstein"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 127972.0,
      "end_time": 129724.0,
      "text": "created for sci-fi."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 129723.99999999999,
      "end_time": 131263.0,
      "text": "Today, we are going to explore all"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 131263.0,
      "end_time": 133622.0,
      "text": "the other ways that\nFrankenstein established tropes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 133622.0,
      "end_time": 136316.0,
      "text": "styles, and techniques that we almost take"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 136316.0,
      "end_time": 138512.0,
      "text": "for granted in sci-fi today."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 138512.0,
      "end_time": 141075.0,
      "text": "Now, before I tread any\nfurther, I should say one thing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 141075.0,
      "end_time": 143970.0,
      "text": "if you only know this\nstory from the movies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 143970.0,
      "end_time": 146709.0,
      "text": "you don't actually know this story at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 146709.0,
      "end_time": 148985.0,
      "text": "The films have little to do with the book,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 148985.0,
      "end_time": 152036.0,
      "text": "and while it is actually a\nreally worthwhile exercise"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 152036.0,
      "end_time": 154385.0,
      "text": "to think about why this\nstory has been interpreted"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 154385.0,
      "end_time": 157649.0,
      "text": "and reimagined the way it has\nthroughout the 20th century."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 157649.0,
      "end_time": 159527.0,
      "text": "everything I talk about today will be"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 159527.0,
      "end_time": 161470.0,
      "text": "regarding the original work."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 161470.0,
      "end_time": 164170.0,
      "text": "So let's start at the\nbeginning, with a young man,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 164170.0,
      "end_time": 166893.0,
      "text": "obsessed by alchemy and yet fascinated by"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 166893.0,
      "end_time": 168628.0,
      "text": "the power of science."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 168628.0,
      "end_time": 171253.0,
      "text": "A young man determined\nto overcome death for"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 171253.0,
      "end_time": 173227.0,
      "text": "the fame it might bring him."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 173227.0,
      "end_time": 175573.0,
      "text": "A young man blind to the consequences of"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 175573.0,
      "end_time": 178074.0,
      "text": "what he is trying to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 178074.0,
      "end_time": 179971.0,
      "text": "Let's talk about Victor Frankenstein."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 179971.0,
      "end_time": 183699.0,
      "text": "Victor is the blueprint for\nthe frustrated scientist trope."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 183699.0,
      "end_time": 186555.0,
      "text": "All of those other scientists\nyou read about in comics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 186555.0,
      "end_time": 189440.0,
      "text": "see in movies, or find\nin the pages of later"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 189440.0,
      "end_time": 192009.0,
      "text": "science fiction, those who\nwould have been so great"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 192009.0,
      "end_time": 194170.0,
      "text": "for the world if the world\nhad only acknowledged"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 194170.0,
      "end_time": 196558.0,
      "text": "their genius, they are all basically"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 196558.0,
      "end_time": 198666.0,
      "text": "riffs on Victor Frankenstein."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 198666.0,
      "end_time": 200399.0,
      "text": "In fact, this has become so common"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 200399.0,
      "end_time": 203242.0,
      "text": "and so ingrained into\npop culture that a lot"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 203242.0,
      "end_time": 205558.0,
      "text": "of these characters pop\nup without their authors"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 205558.0,
      "end_time": 207407.0,
      "text": "even really thinking about the legacy"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 207407.0,
      "end_time": 209310.0,
      "text": "of Victor Frankenstein\nthat they come from."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 209310.0,
      "end_time": 212693.0,
      "text": "Victor is also our model\nof scientific hubris."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 212693.0,
      "end_time": 216077.0,
      "text": "He believes that he can best\ndeath itself by creating"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 216077.0,
      "end_time": 218118.0,
      "text": "life out of the parts of the dead,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 218118.0,
      "end_time": 221067.0,
      "text": "and thinking his own\nintellect to be so superior,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 221067.0,
      "end_time": 224273.0,
      "text": "he doesn't even once\nconsider the ramifications"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 224273.0,
      "end_time": 226920.0,
      "text": "of what he's doing until it's too late."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 226920.0,
      "end_time": 229864.0,
      "text": "He is the model for all of\nthose characters punished"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 229864.0,
      "end_time": 232091.0,
      "text": "for defying the laws of nature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 232091.0,
      "end_time": 234789.0,
      "text": "for the scientist so obsessed\nwith pursuing their ideas"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 234789.0,
      "end_time": 237452.0,
      "text": "that they don't even\nconsider what those ideas"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 237452.0,
      "end_time": 239711.0,
      "text": "might ultimately mean for humanity."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 239711.0,
      "end_time": 241416.0,
      "text": "But he's also a coward."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 241416.0,
      "end_time": 243623.0,
      "text": "At the first sight of his own creation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 243623.0,
      "end_time": 246128.0,
      "text": "he flees because it's physically deformed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 246128.0,
      "end_time": 247857.0,
      "text": "because it's too ugly to look at"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 247857.0,
      "end_time": 250163.0,
      "text": "just the way he made it."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 250163.0,
      "end_time": 252575.0,
      "text": "Which brings us to the monster itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 252575.0,
      "end_time": 255040.0,
      "text": "An innocent, filled\nwith gentle kindness and"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 255040.0,
      "end_time": 258054.0,
      "text": "a love for the world, who\nis rejected at every turn"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 258053.99999999997,
      "end_time": 260336.99999999997,
      "text": "for his physical appearance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 260337.0,
      "end_time": 262821.0,
      "text": "eventually growing callus and cold."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 262821.0,
      "end_time": 265236.0,
      "text": "How many times in science\nfiction have we seen"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 265236.0,
      "end_time": 267878.0,
      "text": "this monster with the heart of gold?"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 267878.0,
      "end_time": 271002.0,
      "text": "I present to you that trope's origins,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 271002.0,
      "end_time": 274075.0,
      "text": "and like many things in\nFrankenstein Shelley explores"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 274075.0,
      "end_time": 276292.0,
      "text": "this trope far more thoroughly than"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 276292.0,
      "end_time": 278376.0,
      "text": "many who would eventually borrow it."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 278376.0,
      "end_time": 281255.0,
      "text": "The monster, outwardly ugly,\nfinds itself continuously"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 281255.0,
      "end_time": 284975.0,
      "text": "rejected by an inwardly ugly humanity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 284975.0,
      "end_time": 287018.0,
      "text": "rejected at birth by Victor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 287018.0,
      "end_time": 288978.0,
      "text": "attacked in the first village he visited,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 288978.0,
      "end_time": 291919.0,
      "text": "turned away by the cottagers he cared for"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 291919.0,
      "end_time": 296309.0,
      "text": "and thus, at last the monster\nturns on humanity itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 296309.0,
      "end_time": 298494.0,
      "text": "This theme of rejection despite offering"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 298494.0,
      "end_time": 302208.0,
      "text": "the best intentions and offering\nsomething truly of worth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 302208.0,
      "end_time": 304479.0,
      "text": "has become not only a\ntheme of science fiction"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 304479.0,
      "end_time": 306661.0,
      "text": "literature but of the geek culture that"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 306661.0,
      "end_time": 308125.0,
      "text": "has grown up around it."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 308125.0,
      "end_time": 310021.0,
      "text": "But part of the reason\nthat we see nobility in"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 310021.0,
      "end_time": 313089.0,
      "text": "the monster is that we\nsee it self educate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 313089.0,
      "end_time": 315009.0,
      "text": "reading the greatest books of the past."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 315009.0,
      "end_time": 317360.0,
      "text": "Mary Shelley saw her work as part of"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 317360.0,
      "end_time": 319710.0,
      "text": "an ongoing tradition\nof Western literature."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 319710.0,
      "end_time": 323709.0,
      "text": "Paradise Lost, Dante, The\nSorrows of Young Werther,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 323709.0,
      "end_time": 326010.0,
      "text": "these are all directly\nreferenced in the work."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 326010.0,
      "end_time": 329268.0,
      "text": "They serve as a foundation,\nas key insights into"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 329268.0,
      "end_time": 331158.0,
      "text": "the character of the Monster,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 331158.0,
      "end_time": 333069.0,
      "text": "and they are things\nthat the writer expects"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 333069.0,
      "end_time": 336530.0,
      "text": "the reader to at least have\na passing familiarity with."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 336530.0,
      "end_time": 338710.0,
      "text": "That's something that would\nbecame part of the genre, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 338710.0,
      "end_time": 342170.0,
      "text": "Works like Hyperion are firmly\ngrounded in that tradition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 342170.0,
      "end_time": 345280.0,
      "text": "borrowing structure from\nCanterbury Tales and The Decameron,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 345280.0,
      "end_time": 347604.0,
      "text": "even taking it's name from a Keats poem."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 347604.0,
      "end_time": 350877.0,
      "text": "Even pieces as odd as Dhalgren\nrely on the mythological"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 350877.0,
      "end_time": 353539.0,
      "text": "and literary tradition of the west."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 353539.0,
      "end_time": 355906.0,
      "text": "There is an expectation\nin science fiction that"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 355906.0,
      "end_time": 357844.0,
      "text": "the reader is well read."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 357844.0,
      "end_time": 360622.0,
      "text": "But there's an on-going\ndebate as to whether sci-fi"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 360622.0,
      "end_time": 364221.0,
      "text": "itself is part of the classic\ntradition or something new,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 364221.0,
      "end_time": 366689.0,
      "text": "and as great works of\nscience fiction pour in"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 366689.0,
      "end_time": 369134.0,
      "text": "from all over the globe,\nbringing in new traditions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 369134.0,
      "end_time": 372012.0,
      "text": "that question becomes even more complex."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 372012.0,
      "end_time": 375069.0,
      "text": "But I should also mention\nhow this tale is told,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 375069.0,
      "end_time": 377217.0,
      "text": "through letters, relating a story told"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 377217.0,
      "end_time": 379818.0,
      "text": "to a young man named Robert by the strange"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 379818.0,
      "end_time": 383399.0,
      "text": "and wild scientist he\nfinds out upon the ice."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 383399.0,
      "end_time": 385368.0,
      "text": "Frankenstein is actually a story within"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 385368.0,
      "end_time": 387501.0,
      "text": "a story within a book."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 387501.0,
      "end_time": 390117.0,
      "text": "The whole work is actually\nan epistolary novel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 390117.0,
      "end_time": 392120.0,
      "text": "although that's easy to forget."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 392120.0,
      "end_time": 393931.0,
      "text": "And this allows us a juxtaposition."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 393931.0,
      "end_time": 396948.0,
      "text": "Simply by having the young\nRobert's story set side"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 396948.0,
      "end_time": 399277.0,
      "text": "by side with Victor's, as a reader,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 399277.0,
      "end_time": 402672.0,
      "text": "we are forced to consider the\neager young explorer's ideals"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 402672.0,
      "end_time": 405633.0,
      "text": "and, far more importantly,\nhis motivations."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 405633.0,
      "end_time": 407673.0,
      "text": "We are forced to contrast\nthem with Victor's"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 407673.0,
      "end_time": 410065.0,
      "text": "just by using this framing device,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 410065.0,
      "end_time": 413370.0,
      "text": "Mary Shelley forces us as\nreaders to think about some"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 413370.0,
      "end_time": 415738.0,
      "text": "of the ideas she wants us to consider."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 415738.0,
      "end_time": 418397.0,
      "text": "And, while we rarely see this\nparticular framing device"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 418397.0,
      "end_time": 421064.0,
      "text": "again, it's important because it kicks off"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 421064.0,
      "end_time": 424530.0,
      "text": "a long tradition of science\nfiction using framing devices,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 424530.0,
      "end_time": 427075.0,
      "text": "especially for the purpose\nof making us question"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 427075.0,
      "end_time": 430786.0,
      "text": "just how reliable the\ncentral narrator really is."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 430786.0,
      "end_time": 432721.0,
      "text": "And finally we have the title,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 432721.0,
      "end_time": 436414.0,
      "text": "or rather the alternate\ntitle, The Modern Prometheus."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 436414.0,
      "end_time": 439384.0,
      "text": "On the surface level, the\nallusion here seems clear,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 439384.0,
      "end_time": 441905.0,
      "text": "Victor breathes life into inanimate flesh"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 441905.0,
      "end_time": 444314.0,
      "text": "and he brings knowledge at great cost,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 444314.0,
      "end_time": 447309.0,
      "text": "which would certainly qualify\nhim as The Modern Prometheus"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 447309.0,
      "end_time": 450834.0,
      "text": "but the novel makes a point\nof the fact that he never"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 450834.0,
      "end_time": 454689.0,
      "text": "actually shares that knowledge,\nno one ever finds out"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 454689.0,
      "end_time": 457706.0,
      "text": "how he made his reanimated man."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 457706.0,
      "end_time": 460335.0,
      "text": "So the Prometheus label\ndoesn't entirely fit him."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 460335.0,
      "end_time": 462201.0,
      "text": "But if not Victor, then who is this"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 462201.0,
      "end_time": 464622.0,
      "text": "alternate title referring to?"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 464622.0,
      "end_time": 467056.0,
      "text": "It refers to the scientific method."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 467056.0,
      "end_time": 469871.0,
      "text": "It's this approach to the\nworld that offers us so much,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 469871.0,
      "end_time": 473707.0,
      "text": "that brings mankind so\nmuch, but at what cost?"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 473707.0,
      "end_time": 476938.0,
      "text": "In the end, what will be\nthe price of such marvels?"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 476938.0,
      "end_time": 480722.0,
      "text": "We are asked this time and\ntime again in science fiction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 480722.0,
      "end_time": 483071.0,
      "text": "it's one of sci-fi's most enduring themes."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 483071.0,
      "end_time": 486086.0,
      "text": "From the Martian Chronicles,\nto Pump 6, Terminator,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 486086.0,
      "end_time": 488817.0,
      "text": "to the Matrix we see it\nagain and again and again."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 488817.0,
      "end_time": 491108.0,
      "text": "And I think It's important to note,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 491108.0,
      "end_time": 493597.0,
      "text": "the alternate title isn't The New Icarus."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 493597.0,
      "end_time": 496820.0,
      "text": "Prometheus's story isn't a\nflew too close to the sun,"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 496820.0,
      "end_time": 499413.0,
      "text": "brought about your own\ndestruction cautionary tale."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 499413.0,
      "end_time": 502900.0,
      "text": "In Prometheus's story, he\ndoes suffer for his actions"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 502900.0,
      "end_time": 505667.0,
      "text": "but his sacrifice benefits us all."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 505667.0,
      "end_time": 508162.0,
      "text": "The greatest good comes\nthrough that sacrifice."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 508162.0,
      "end_time": 510782.0,
      "text": "These books, these works\nof art that examine"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 510782.0,
      "end_time": 514020.0,
      "text": "the farthest edge of where\nour science might lead us"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 514020.0,
      "end_time": 517882.0,
      "text": "can be cautionary tales while\nsimultaneously celebrating"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 517881.99999999994,
      "end_time": 521823.99999999994,
      "text": "science, daring us to push\nahead as far and as fast"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 521823.99999999994,
      "end_time": 525003.0,
      "text": "as we can while, at the\nsame time, urging us"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 525003.0,
      "end_time": 527099.0,
      "text": "to be wiser than their protagonists."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 527099.0,
      "end_time": 529852.0,
      "text": "So now that we're on firm\nground with Frankenstein's place"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 529852.0,
      "end_time": 532829.0,
      "text": "in the history of science\nfiction, join us next week"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 532829.0,
      "end_time": 535001.0,
      "text": "as we begin to talk\nabout all the other works"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 535001.0,
      "end_time": 537780.0,
      "text": "that Shelley references\nthroughout this great piece,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 537780.0,
      "end_time": 540677.0,
      "text": "and as we discuss how those works help us"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 540677.0,
      "end_time": 543177.0,
      "text": "to better understand her own."
    }
  ]
}